  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Water Security in the Pacific SIDS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pacific SIDS are highly vulnerable to climate change and water related extreme events. Small changes and shocks resulting from natural hazards, climate variability, climate change and human development can have huge impacts. Water security is thus a high priority for ensuring the on-going sustainable development of Pacific SIDS with most requiring support in all elements of Integrated Water Resources Management. Working in partnership with other UN and regional IGOs, UNESCO will focus on bringing technical expertise to bear on particularly intransigent problems that fall within its areas of expertise. It will provide opportunities for Pacific engagement in the International Hydrology Programme(IHP) and collaborate to improve hydrological services and strengthen water capacities.</narrative>
  </description>
